    "64 Perhaps all the \"stable objects\" (including organisms) that we see are just the lowdimensional hub nodes -the medium bearing the pattern, and it's the persistent, deep pattern that is the true agent.",
    "This links to ideas we are developing on the active Platonic Space concept, which focuses attention on the patterns and their interactions, not the media which they temporarily animate.",
    "On this view, we are just slightly coarser variants of our memories, all essentially denizens of Platonic space, projected temporarily into low-dimensional media.",
    "65 How differently and for how long?",
    "That is a matter of degree, determined by (and determining) the system's cognitive light cone -the spatio-temporal distance of events, from the here-and-now, that are needed to have a powerful understanding of a system."
